The Archbishop was flown to the Seychelles and only allowed to return when he had abandoned his "enosis" movement, demanding union between Cyprus and Greece.  77 years ago (1945) The US Air Force launched Operation Meetinghouse, a devastating firebomb attack on the Japanese capital Tokyo. More than 100,000 civilians were killed by bombs dropped from 279 B-29 Superfortresses and the eastern part of the city was destroyed. It was the deadliest air raid of the Second World War  53 years ago (1969) James Earl Ray was jailed for 99 years for the murder of US civil rights leader Martin Luther King Jr. He was spared the electric chair after pleading guilty but three days after his incarceration he recanted and claimed he had been set up. He died in prison in 1998.